          \"timestamp\": 1776212651715,\n          \"provenance\": {\n            \"kind\": \"inter_session\",\n            \"sourceSessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e\",\n            \"sourceTool\": \"sessions_send\"\n          },\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"df5c0d46\",\n            \"seq\": 1421\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"Night silence period - between 23:00-07:00 UTC+7 (which is 16:00-00:00 UTC). Wait, 00:22 UTC = 07:22 UTC+7 which is past the morning threshold of 07:00. But actually the night silence rule says \\\"23:00–07:00 UTC+7\\\" which is \\\"16:00-00:00 UTC\\\". Currently it's 00:22 UTC = 07:22 UTC+7. So we're past the silence window (07:00+7) and before 23:00+7... wait that's not right.\\n\\nLet me recalculate. \\n\\nSo the night silence is from 23:00 to 07:00 UTC+7, which translates to 16:00 to 00:00 UTC. At 00:22 UTC, we're outside that window and it's 07:22 in UTC+7, so the silence period has ended.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"HEARTBEAT_OK\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 231,\n            \"output\": 207,\n            \"totalTokens\": 53471,\n            \"cacheRead\": 0,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 53033,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776212651871,\n          \"responseId\": \"062e0daed4e0d9b5e24fdf1f834169d8\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"5046c7e4\",\n            \"seq\": 1422\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"origin\": {\n        \"provider\": \"heartbeat\"\n      },\n      \"label\": \"Cron: 5p Progress Report - DTLX\",\n      \"displayName\": \"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1776212642198,\n      \"sessionId\": \"3843774a-ce82-41d7-b34c-a2b42d60df56\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 45332,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"running\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1776199558073,\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/3843774a-ce82-41d7-b34c-a2b42d60df56.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"The memory_get returned \\\"disabled\\\": true, which means memory retrieval is unavailable. Let me check the heartbeat-state.json file directly using the read tool.\\n\\nLet me analyze the current state vs what I can see from the sessions list:\\n\\n**Current active sessions (from sessions_list):**\\n1. `cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31` — **running** — DTLX 5p progress monitor (this cron)\\n2. `cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e` — **running** — Agent Status to Lead\\n\\n\\n3. `cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7` — **running** — QLHV 5p progress monitor\\n4. `cron:53c5832a-eecc-4d6b-a4c3-d1b78a430dca` — no status field visible (the \\\"Daily Briefing 5AM UTC+7\\\" cron)\\n\\nNow I'm looking at the telegram sessions — there's a direct message to 6053576134 that ended at 1776212660, and I'm checking the Telegram group sessions.\\n\\nI'm also seeing a group session for -5163901258 that's still running, though it ended at 1776163783190, and another group session for -5168104492 that's marked as done. The main session appears to be cut off.\\n\\nLooking at the remaining agent sessions, there are several subagents across different models that have all completed with either timeout or error statuses, including backend, frontend, and UI/UX roles. There's also a cron session with an unknown status that's been running for about 13 hours.\\n\\nI'm also seeing additional cron sessions that are still active, including a QLHV report cron from earlier today and another session with a Telegram label that's been running for nearly a full day. There are more subagents with various statuses to account for as well. I'm seeing the pattern now — the cron jobs are cycling through, with e7885813 restarting at 00:19 and ed2d0b5d being a recurring 5-minute job that should have triggered several times by now, though the last one I saw ended at 17:08 UTC. I'm checking the heartbeat state from memory, but it's unavailable due to disabled access. Let me pull the file directly to compare the baseline.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_function_6duip1cu90jj_1\",\n              \"name\": \"read\",\n              \"arguments\": {\n                \"path\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/heartbeat-state.json\"\n              }\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 30100,\n            \"output\": 557,\n            \"totalTokens\": 45010,\n            \"cacheRead\": 13944,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 409,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n          \"time