running for about 13 hours.\n\nI'm also seeing additional cron sessions that are still active, including a QLHV report cron from earlier today and another session with a Telegram label that's been running for nearly a full day. There are more subagents with various statuses to account for as well. I'm seeing the pattern now — the cron jobs are cycling through, with e7885813 restarting at 00:19 and ed2d0b5d being a recurring 5-minute job that should have triggered several times by now, though the last one I saw ended at 17:08 UTC. I'm checking the heartbeat state from memory, but it's unavailable due to disabled access. Let me pull the file directly to compare the baseline."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6duip1cu90jj_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/heartbeat-state.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":30100,"output":557,"totalTokens":45010,"cacheRead":13944,"cacheWrite":409,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776212700712,"responseId":"062e0dde8c18856b0ee70aaa702242d7","__openclaw":{"id":"0c437747","seq":5}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the last known state from 00:14 UTC. Let me compare with the current state (00:24 UTC).\n\n**Baseline (00:14 UTC):**\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` — running ✅\n- `cron:e7885813` — running ✅\n- `cron:6f3323ef` — running ✅\n- `cron:53c5832a` — done ✅\n- `main` — done ✅\n- `telegram:direct:6053576134` — done ✅\n- `telegram:group:-5163901258` — running ✅\n\n\n- **Pipeline: HEALTHY, blockers: []**\n\nLooking at the current state (00:24 UTC), all the cron jobs are still running as expected with no changes to the main or telegram sessions, though `cron:e7885813` appears to have restarted as part of its normal cycle.\n\nThe pipeline remains healthy with no blockers, so the overall system status hasn't changed—no new failures, new sessions, or new blockers have appeared, and all previously identified subagent failures from AHV Works are already accounted for in the baseline.\n\nSince nothing has shifted, I'm staying silent. Let me double-check that `cron:e7885813` is actually still running and hasn't died without me noticing. it says status: running, but the telegram session it references shows ended at 1776212660602, which is 00:17 UTC—so that agent status cron likely ran and sent its message through the telegram session before completing. That's expected behavior for a one-shot cron job.\n\nThe state is stable, so I'm staying silent."},{"type":"text","text":"Comparing against baseline (00:14 UTC 15 Apr):\n\n**Baseline:** cron:ed2d0b5d ✅ cron:e7885813 ✅ cron:6f3323ef ✅ cron:53c5832a done ✅ main done ✅ telegram:direct done ✅ telegram:group:-5163901258 running ✅ — pipeline HEALTHY, blockers: none\n\n**Current (00:24 UTC):** All 4 crons still running. telegram:direct still done. telegram:group:-5163901258 still running. All unchanged.\n\n**No new failures. No new sessions spawned. No sessions died. No blockers. Pipeline stable.**\n\nSilent."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":427,"output":476,"totalTokens":45808,"cacheRead":14264,"cacheWrite":30641,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776212714966,"responseId":"062e0dec83f3941fb349f1e361e373c5","__openclaw":{"id":"d58a83e9","seq":7}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","label":"Cron: Agent Status to Lead","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1776212534676,"sessionId":"56f4963d-308d-4c94-89a2-457d5f430fc4","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":45370,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"running","startedAt":1776211909894,"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":